text: Kaltymanovo () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Kaltymanovsky Selsoviet, Iglinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 530 as of 2010. There are 4 streets. == Geography == It is located 18 km from Iglino. == References == Category:Rural localities in Iglinsky District
title: Kaltymanovo
